WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:41.000
DIN

2
00:00:57.141 --> 00:01:01.185
Earth 
Birthplace of the human race.

3
00:01:02.604 --> 00:01:05.481
A species much like our own.

4
00:01:06.316 --> 00:01:08.985
Capable of great compassion...

5
00:01:10.696 --> 00:01:12.697
and great violence.

6
00:01:23.333 --> 00:01:26.794
For in our quest to protect the humans.

7
00:01:26.879 --> 00:01:29.922
a deeper revelation dawns.

8
00:01:30.007 --> 00:01:33.176
Our worlds have met before.

9
00:02:18.639 --> 00:02:21.974
- Newsflash from the BBC.
- Breaking news out of Shanghai.

10
00:02:22.059 --> 00:02:26.103
There's been a major toxic spill
in the Shanghai factory district.

11
00:02:26.188 --> 00:02:28.314
We're staying on top of this developing story for you.

12
00:02:28.398 --> 00:02:31.859
We will bring you any new information as we get it.

13
00:02:36.532 --> 00:02:39.242
NEST Seahawks approaching target.

14
00:02:39.326 --> 00:02:42.578
Three minutes until evacuation is complete. sir.

15
00:02:43.372 --> 00:02:46.707
Chinese airspace has been locked and sealed.
one-mile radius.

16
00:02:46.792 --> 00:02:48.835
All right. give NEST team the go.

17
00:02:48.919 --> 00:02:50.711
Black Hawks. you're clear to land.

18
00:02:52.005 --> 00:02:55.049
Ding-a-ling!
Come out and get your ice cream.

19
00:02:57.719 --> 00:03:01.597
Any bad robot out there
better get ready for an ass-whupping.

20
00:03:07.271 --> 00:03:10.940
For the last two years.
an advance team of new Autobots

21
00:03:11.024 --> 00:03:14.277
has taken refuge here
under my command.

22
00:03:14.695 --> 00:03:16.195
Arcees. get ready to launch.

23
00:03:16.280 --> 00:03:17.822
We're locked and loaded.

24
00:03:17.906 --> 00:03:21.951
Together. we form an alliance with the humans.

25
00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:25.204
a secret but brave squad of soldiers.

26
00:03:25.289 --> 00:03:28.207
All right. listen up.
China's cover story on this one is "toxic spill"

27
00:03:28.292 --> 00:03:30.543
They had to evac the area for search and rescue.

28
00:03:30.627 --> 00:03:33.129
This makes six enemy contacts in eight months.

29
00:03:33.213 --> 00:03:36.424
We gotta make sure this one does not get out in the public eye.
so keep it tight.

30
00:03:36.967 --> 00:03:40.720
A classified strike team called NEST.

31
00:03:40.804 --> 00:03:44.390
We hunt for what remains
of our Decepticon foes

32
00:03:44.474 --> 00:03:47.518
hiding in different countries
around the globe.

33
00:03:47.603 --> 00:03:48.936
Roll in Alpha through Echo now.

34
00:03:58.906 --> 00:04:00.156
Move out! Let's go!

35
00:04:17.674 --> 00:04:21.761
All right. Ironhide.
We got echoes. They're close.

36
00:04:22.763 --> 00:04:24.764
Steel stacks at 2 o'clock.

37
00:04:36.068 --> 00:04:39.528
He's here.
I smell him.

38
00:04:43.909 --> 00:04:46.035
It's close. It's getting closer.

39
00:04:50.874 --> 00:04:53.209
- Oh. no.
- What have you got?

40
00:04:53.919 --> 00:04:55.544
Thermal ripple.

41
00:04:57.631 --> 00:05:00.549
Right. everybody. be steady.
We're right on top of it.

42
00:05:12.729 --> 00:05:14.397
Eagle niner!

43
00:05:14.481 --> 00:05:16.190
I need an energy proton.

44
00:05:30.288 --> 00:05:32.873
Panther 1.
requesting fire mission now!

45
00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:35.376
Gunships on station.
Roll in hot!

46
00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:37.253
Dog 1. now we are engaging.

47
00:05:46.596 --> 00:05:47.805
We got a second Decepticon.

48
00:05:50.892 --> 00:05:53.686
Arcee twins! Target coming your way!

49
00:05:58.400 --> 00:06:00.151
I got him. I got him!

50
00:06:30.223 --> 00:06:33.225
I screwed that up.
I'm okay. I'm all right.

51
00:06:33.310 --> 00:06:35.519
- This is combat. man.
- Total brain freeze. man.

52
00:06:35.604 --> 00:06:36.645
What's wrong with you?

53
00:06:40.317 --> 00:06:42.151
Bring in Sideswipe!

54
00:06:43.945 --> 00:06:45.488
Clear a path!

55
00:07:01.338 --> 00:07:02.671
Damn. I'm good!

56
00:07:12.140 --> 00:07:15.476
Air support. we need Big Buddha
to deliver the drop now!

57
00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:17.978
Cyclone 98. final attack hitting in 120.

58
00:07:18.063 --> 00:07:22.316
Clear to drop in
five. four. three. two. one.

59
00:07:35.539 --> 00:07:38.666
Autobots. I'm in pursuit!

60
00:08:07.404 --> 00:08:08.821
Pull over!

61
00:08:29.551 --> 00:08:31.886
Punk-ass Decepticon!

62
00:08:31.970 --> 00:08:34.305
Any last words?

63
00:08:34.389 --> 00:08:38.100
This is not your planet to rule!

64
00:08:38.185 --> 00:08:40.519
The Fallen shall rise again.

65
00:08:42.230 --> 00:08:43.689
That doesn't sound good.

66
00:08:43.899 --> 00:08:45.900
Not today.

67
00:08:51.156 --> 00:08:53.532
Come on. let's go!
All hands on deck!

68
00:08:53.617 --> 00:08:56.368
Frankie. Mojo. out!
Come on. kiddo. we're on a schedule.

69
00:08:56.453 --> 00:08:58.954
Slow down. Dad.
Why are you in such a hurry to get rid of me?

70
00:08:59.039 --> 00:09:01.665
- Did you rent the room out?
- No. I got other ideas for your room

71
00:09:01.750 --> 00:09:03.918
and it rhymes with "home theater"

72
00:09:09.090 --> 00:09:12.801
Look what I found.
It's your little baby booties.

73
00:09:13.845 --> 00:09:17.264
- Ma.
- My little baby-bootie boy.

74
00:09:17.349 --> 00:09:19.141
- You can't go.
- You see this. Dad? This is how

75
00:09:19.226 --> 00:09:20.559
you're supposed to react
when the fruit of your loins

76
00:09:20.644 --> 00:09:22.937
goes out into the cruel world
to fend for himself. okay?

77
00:09:23.021 --> 00:09:25.481
Yeah. my heart bleeds for you. pal.
College. bummer!

78
00:09:25.565 --> 00:09:29.568
You have to come home every holiday.
not just big ones.

79
00:09:29.653 --> 00:09:31.654
You have to come home for Halloween.

80
00:09:31.738 --> 00:09:32.988
Well. I can't come home for Halloween. Mom.

81
00:09:33.073 --> 00:09:34.490
- Well. then we'll come to you.
- You're not coming.

82
00:09:34.574 --> 00:09:35.741
- No. we're not going anywhere.
- We'll dress up.

83
00:09:35.825 --> 00:09:37.117
We'll be in costumes.
You'll never know it's us.

84
00:09:37.202 --> 00:09:38.786
- You can't do that. Mom.
- Would you let the kid breathe.

85
00:09:38.870 --> 00:09:40.663
for crying out loud?
Come on. Go pack.

86
00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:42.248
There's no way you're packed
for a month-long trip.

87
00:09:42.332 --> 00:09:45.626
Come on. chop. chop!
Let's go. March. young lady.

88
00:09:46.753 --> 00:09:48.420
- Dad.
- I love it when you call me "young lady"

89
00:09:48.505 --> 00:09:50.589
- you dirty old man.
- You ain't seen nothing yet.

90
00:09:50.674 --> 00:09:52.716
- Dad. Dad. Dad. whoa!
- What?

91
00:09:52.801 --> 00:09:55.177
I'm watching what you're doing. Dad.
It's not a rap video.

92
00:09:55.262 --> 00:09:56.595
It's just like a coach thing.

93
00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:58.555
That was a really creepy move just now. Dad.

94
00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:03.769
Look. You know. your mother and me
are really proud of you.

95
00:10:03.853 --> 00:10:06.272
You're the first Witwicky
ever to go to college.

96
00:10:06.356 --> 00:10:10.025
Now I'm crying again!
This sucks!

97
00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:11.902
You're gonna be okay. Ma.

98
00:10:11.987 --> 00:10:13.445
You know. it's just going to be.

99
00:10:13.530 --> 00:10:19.285
you know. hard for her to accept
that her boy's all grown up. you know.

100
00:10:19.369 --> 00:10:22.329
going out to handle the world on his own.

101
00:10:22.414 --> 00:10:24.665
- You okay. Pop?
- Yeah.

102
00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:27.293
Mojo. no dominating Frankie!

103
00:10:27.377 --> 00:10:30.713
Get the hell off the couch.
you filthy beasts!

104
00:10:30.797 --> 00:10:32.840
You'll see a lot of that in college. too.

105
00:10:32.924 --> 00:10:36.093
- What are you talking about. Dad?
- There's gonna be a lot of women there.

106
00:10:36.177 --> 00:10:37.803
Yeah. well.
I'm a one-woman kind of guy.

107
00:10:37.887 --> 00:10:39.263
Look. Mikaela's the greatest.

108
00:10:39.347 --> 00:10:41.974
but you gotta give each other
room to grow. okay?

109
00:10:42.058 --> 00:10:44.310
You're no different
than any other couple your age.

110
00:10:44.394 --> 00:10:46.562
Except we discovered
an alien race together.

111
00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:48.063
How long you gonna be riding that scooter?

112
00:10:58.950 --> 00:11:02.077
Dad. listen. I know what the odds are.
We're the exception. okay?

113
00:11:02.162 --> 00:11:04.997
Wait a second.
Who could that be?

114
00:11:05.081 --> 00:11:06.915
In two weeks. it could be Muffy.

115
00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:08.250
Hey. beautiful.

116
00:11:08.585 --> 00:11:10.544
- I'm breaking up with you. Sam.
- Really?

117
00:11:10.628 --> 00:11:12.087
You sure?
I'm not hearing a lot of conviction.

118
00:11:12.172 --> 00:11:15.758
Well. I am. okay?
So. there's no reason for me to come say good-bye to you.

119
00:11:16.217 --> 00:11:18.093
Wow. you almost sounded serious
that time.

120
00:11:18.762 --> 00:11:22.014
Guess what?
I made you a long-distance relationship kit.

121
00:11:22.098 --> 00:11:24.516
Yeah. I got you a webcam.
so we can chat 24/7.

122
00:11:24.601 --> 00:11:25.768
All Witwicky. all the time.

123
00:11:26.186 --> 00:11:27.853
And I got you a couple souvenirs
from the event

124
00:11:27.937 --> 00:11:29.188
that cannot be mentioned on cell phones.

125
00:11:29.272 --> 00:11:32.775
- Some mixes and candles and stuff.
- Sounds cute. I can't wait.

126
00:11:33.068 --> 00:11:35.194
Hey! You want the infamous D-Day shirt?

127
00:11:35.278 --> 00:11:37.446
You kept your nasty. shredded clothes?

128
00:11:37.655 --> 00:11:39.031
Yeah. Of course. I kept it. Mikaela.

129
00:11:39.115 --> 00:11:41.158
It's like my Super Bowl jersey.
I bled in this thing.

130
00:11:41.242 --> 00:11:43.869
- Wow. You're pretty confident. huh?
- No. it's not that.

131
00:11:43.953 --> 00:11:46.372
It's just that my low self-esteem's
at an all-time high.

132
00:11:46.748 --> 00:11:49.708
You think your little box of souvenirs
is gonna keep me from leaving you?

133
00:11:50.293 --> 00:11:51.335
You really should come with me.

134
00:11:51.419 --> 00:11:53.170
They got cheap apartments
near campus.

135
00:11:53.254 --> 00:11:56.799
Well. that's not gonna happen
until I get my man-child father.

136
00:11:56.883 --> 00:11:59.551
fresh out of prison. back on his feet.

137
00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:01.929
I heard that.
Where'd you put the clutch covers?

138
00:12:02.013 --> 00:12:04.390
- Next to the camshafts.
- I love it when you say "camshafts"

139
00:12:04.474 --> 00:12:05.516
Whisper it to me.

140
00:12:08.144 --> 00:12:09.853
Camshafts

141
00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:12.022
Why can't I hate you?

142
00:12:12.982 --> 00:12:14.942
It's my Witwicky charm.

143
00:12:15.485 --> 00:12:16.735
Wait. hold on.
Wait. hold on a second.

144
00:12:16.820 --> 00:12:19.738
I guess we're not breaking up.
I'll be over in 20.

145
00:12:19.823 --> 00:12:23.492
Mikaela. I think a sliver of the Cube
got stuck on my shirt.

146
00:12:28.957 --> 00:12:30.040
Sam?

147
00:12:38.133 --> 00:12:39.174
There's a fire!

148
00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:41.427
Dad. we got a fire!

149
00:13:00.280 --> 00:13:01.488
Fire!

150
00:13:11.541 --> 00:13:14.168
Ron. did you know it was gonna be this hard?

151
00:13:14.252 --> 00:13:15.794
Can you just stop?

152
00:13:15.879 --> 00:13:18.589
Yeah. okay. I'll stop.
You carry this shit!

153
00:13:28.975 --> 00:13:30.225
- Wow.
- Do you know what?

154
00:13:30.310 --> 00:13:31.560
- What?
- I don't want to go anywhere with you.

155
00:13:31.644 --> 00:13:32.811
I don't wanna go to France with you.

156
00:13:32.896 --> 00:13:34.438
I don't wanna go
around the corner with you.

157
00:13:34.522 --> 00:13:35.814
- I'm going back inside.
- All right. fine.

158
00:13:35.899 --> 00:13:36.940
I'll call you from Paris.

159
00:13:49.037 --> 00:13:50.829
What is all the racket?

160
00:13:50.914 --> 00:13:51.914
Sam?

161
00:13:52.582 --> 00:13:54.374
Dad!

162
00:13:59.923 --> 00:14:01.840
- What was that?
- That's the whole kitchen!

163
00:14:04.677 --> 00:14:07.429
- Bumblebee... Oh. my...
- Bumblebee!

164
00:14:26.824 --> 00:14:29.868
- 911.
- Bumblebee!

165
00:14:30.620 --> 00:14:32.871
- Get in the garage. Go!
- What the freak just happened?

166
00:14:32.956 --> 00:14:37.209
I'm about to have a nervous breakdown.
Just go in the garage quietly. please.

167
00:14:37.293 --> 00:14:38.794
Holy Mother!

168
00:14:41.756 --> 00:14:44.800
- Oh. my God!
- Whatever.

169
00:14:44.884 --> 00:14:47.052
Get in the garage now!

170
00:14:52.642 --> 00:14:55.227
- Firemen! Fire fighters. over here!
- Dogs out! Get the dogs out!

171
00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:59.022
This is it! Come on. you guys.
What are you waiting for?

172
00:15:04.696 --> 00:15:06.697
My house is on fire!

173
00:15:10.159 --> 00:15:12.202
...very important.
What happened?

174
00:15:12.287 --> 00:15:16.999
Come here. Listen. I need you to take
the Cube sliver and put it in your purse.

175
00:15:17.083 --> 00:15:18.250
- What's going on?
- Just take it.

176
00:15:18.334 --> 00:15:20.252
- Sam Witwicky. a word with you.
- Yes. Mom. Yeah.

177
00:15:20.336 --> 00:15:22.504
- Hi. Mikaela. I have a bald spot.
- Hi.

178
00:15:22.589 --> 00:15:24.965
- An old furnace. I think.
- From a waffle iron.

179
00:15:25.049 --> 00:15:28.594
When you go. he goes. I cannot live
with a psychotic alien in my garage!

180
00:15:28.678 --> 00:15:31.346
Judy...
National security.

181
00:15:31.431 --> 00:15:34.975
Look. if we stay quiet.
they're gonna take care of everything.

182
00:15:35.059 --> 00:15:38.395
Just consider this
the official start of our remodel. okay?

183
00:15:38.479 --> 00:15:41.523
Fine. If the government's paying.
I want a pool and a hot tub!

184
00:15:41.608 --> 00:15:44.067
And I'm gonna skinny-dip
and you can't say shit about it!

185
00:15:47.864 --> 00:15:51.283
- Yeah. you know you're in trouble.
- He still having voice problems?

186
00:15:51.367 --> 00:15:53.785
He's playing it up.

187
00:15:53.870 --> 00:15:56.955
Bee. I want to talk to you
about the college thing. okay?

188
00:15:57.040 --> 00:16:00.292
I'm so excited and I just can't hide it

189
00:16:00.376 --> 00:16:02.502
Hey. I'm not taking you with me.

190
00:16:03.963 --> 00:16:06.340
I'm gonna wait outside. okay?

191
00:16:08.009 --> 00:16:09.176
I meant to tell you about this earlier.

192
00:16:09.260 --> 00:16:11.720
It's just that. you know...
Here's the thing.

193
00:16:11.804 --> 00:16:14.014
Freshmen aren't allowed to have cars.

194
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:17.100
I know. and if it was up to me.
I'd take you with me. but it's not. Bee.

195
00:16:17.185 --> 00:16:19.978
Look. You're an Autobot.
You shouldn't be living in my dad's garage.

196
00:16:20.063 --> 00:16:24.441
I mean. you're suffocating in here.
You deserve better than this.

197
00:16:24.525 --> 00:16:25.984
This is hard enough. man.
Don't make it harder.

198
00:16:26.069 --> 00:16:28.445
Can you just look at me. please?

199
00:16:29.739 --> 00:16:32.908
Come on. big guy.
Look. the guardian thing is done.

200
00:16:32.992 --> 00:16:36.328
Okay? You did yourjob.
Look. I'm safe now.

201
00:16:36.412 --> 00:16:38.872
You need to go be with
Optimus Prime and the others.

202
00:16:38.956 --> 00:16:42.334
I just want to be normal. Bee.
That's why I'm going to college.

203
00:16:42.418 --> 00:16:44.586
and I can't do that with you.

204
00:16:45.296 --> 00:16:47.506
It's not the last time I'm gonna see you.
you know. Bee.

205
00:16:47.590 --> 00:16:51.385
Come on. don't do that. Bee.
You're killing me. Bee.

206
00:16:52.970 --> 00:16:55.597
But you'll always be my first car.

207
00:16:57.475 --> 00:16:59.142
Love you. Bee.

208
00:17:04.899 --> 00:17:05.982
Wow!

209
00:17:06.192 --> 00:17:09.236
Between State Farm and the taxpayers.
we're all taken care of.

210
00:17:09.320 --> 00:17:10.821
- You got dirt all over you.
- Stop. Stop.

211
00:17:10.905 --> 00:17:12.406
- What?
- Stop. I'm okay.

212
00:17:12.490 --> 00:17:13.865
Look.

213
00:17:14.325 --> 00:17:17.202
So. you think you can make it through
those East Coast winters without me?

214
00:17:17.286 --> 00:17:19.538
You're the best thing
to ever happen to me.

215
00:17:19.622 --> 00:17:22.624
- And?
- And I'll do anything for you.

216
00:17:23.376 --> 00:17:24.543
And?

217
00:17:24.627 --> 00:17:27.713
- I think Sam's about to say the L-word.
- Let's go. kiddo!

218
00:17:27.797 --> 00:17:28.880
Nice timing. Dad.

219
00:17:29.298 --> 00:17:30.966
I adore you.

220
00:17:32.385 --> 00:17:33.385
That's not the word that I want

221
00:17:33.469 --> 00:17:34.886
- to hear right now.
- What are you talking about?

222
00:17:34.971 --> 00:17:35.971
It's the same word as the other word.

223
00:17:36.055 --> 00:17:37.889
- It's not the same word.
- Look. if I say the other word now

224
00:17:37.974 --> 00:17:39.516
and you forced me to say it.
it won't mean anything. plus

225
00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:41.852
you haven't said it either.
So. don't get mad at me for not saying it.

226
00:17:41.936 --> 00:17:44.521
Yeah. but I haven't said it because guys
always run when you say it first.

227
00:17:44.605 --> 00:17:48.233
Yeah. well. so do girls.
Especially girls like you. with options.

228
00:17:48.317 --> 00:17:52.487
So. this is all part of your elaborate plan
to keep me interested?

229
00:17:53.281 --> 00:17:56.158
- It can be.
- I hate that it's working.

230
00:17:57.285 --> 00:17:58.994
Can I have a kiss?

231
00:17:59.620 --> 00:18:01.830
We're going to make it work. I promise.

232
00:18:34.947 --> 00:18:38.950
Soundwave acknowledges.
Pursue her.

233
00:18:39.035 --> 00:18:41.036
Retrieve it.

234
00:19:02.767 --> 00:19:05.602
Autobot twins. report to Hangar Three.

235
00:19:06.771 --> 00:19:08.522
Bad-ass ice-cream truck
coming through.

236
00:19:08.606 --> 00:19:10.482
- Excuse me! Excuse me! Hello!
- No. I don't...

